[I] A utility to set power features of ATA drives in FreeBSD and Linux

[T] ATAidle is a utility to set the power management features of ATA hard
[T] drives in FreeBSD and Linux, including idle and standby timeouts,
[T] APM, and acoustic level settings. It can also show details about the
[T] installed devices.

